Welcome to multidisciplinary creator @gabrielle_rosenstein‚Äôs (Gabrielle Rosenstein) sci-femme fantasy: ‚Äúa universe of super-curvy, hyper-girlie, strong and cool chrome characters‚Äù that spans digital and physical realms. 
 
Gabrielle‚Äôs hyper-stylized depictions of the female form serve as ‚Äúa metaphor for the hidden power that lies within seemingly unassuming cuteness and the multifaceted essence of femme energy.‚Äù 
 
‚ÄúMy designs inherently reflect my queer identity ‚Äî a love letter to women, a crush, an alter ego, an extension of my very being. My 3D characters started off as bare-bodied silhouettes, acting as the garments, but the progression of world-building led to customizing outfits and accessories fit for their future-cute galaxy.‚Äù 
 
The organic evolution of this universe has surpassed digital bounds, culminating in the launch of Gabrielle‚Äôs FW23 collection, ‚ÄúCharm‚Äù ‚Äî bringing her 3D sci-femme universe to life through wearable accessories including bags, key charms and charm bracelets. 
 
‚ÄúThrough my collection, I invite everyone to join in the escapism and unlock their authentic sci-dentities and bring a tangible piece of life the journey back to the physi world.‚Äù

‚ÄúI am incredibly proud of who I am and where I come from. As a descendent of storytellers, I‚Äôve felt a responsibility from a young age to preserve and pass on stories of survivance and celebration.‚Äù ‚ÄîDin√© (Navajo) poet, educator and playwright @kinsalehues (Kinsale Drake)
 
‚ÄúIndigenous peoples are often framed in a negative light due to stereotype, underrepresentation, miseducation and tragic narratives, but my work seeks to find joy, futurities and the beauty of our survivance,‚Äù says Kinsale, whose first book, ‚ÄúThe Sky Was Once A Dark Blanket,‚Äù a collection about Native music, won the 2023 National Poetry Series.
 
Kinsale is also the director of NDN Girls Book Club. ‚ÄúWe platform Indigenous authors, support Native youth in their creative endeavors nationwide, provide free writing workshops, provide books for tribal libraries and reading circles and send out Native literature for free. 
 
Collectivity is powerful; supporting one another makes a world of difference. My work is ultimately for my community and to make them proud.‚Äù

Belgian ceramic artist and fashion designer @naomigilon (Naomi Gilon) creates contemporary chimeras ‚Äî unique anthropomorphic hybrid objects that mix fantasy, terror and sublimity.

‚ÄúAll my pieces are handmade, with no molding involved, using either stoneware or porcelain. Bags and other accessories, or body sculptures, are wearable ‚Äî that's the goal. They go beyond the static contemplation of ‚Äòart.‚Äô‚Äù

Naomi has developed a signature obsession in her work. ‚ÄúThese monstrous hands ‚Äî with long claws, neither human nor animal, something beyond us ‚Äî draw inspiration from car customization, manga, science fiction, horror films, the image of the rock star and myths. However, my reflections are more related to society, human behavior, scientific advances, crises, etc.

Myths are full of monsters. Monsters reflect our fears, and horror seeks to evoke fear and insecurity within each of us.‚Äù

Photos and videos by @naomigilon

@tayakun (Taya Lindsey) needs no excuse to put together a special look. 
 
‚ÄúI love dressing up, whether it‚Äôs for going to work, the gas station or an anime convention. I love expressing myself through the way I dress ‚Äî it could be with makeup, accessories or just the whole outfit. It shows people that I‚Äôm going to dress the way I want, whether they like it or not.‚Äù 
 
Taya‚Äôs love of cosplay and anime helps them build on outfits they‚Äôve previously worn. ‚ÄúI think about what can make this one better, what can I add to this piece and just do a lot of mixing and matching.

‚ÄúSometimes I think I‚Äôm not goated, but then I take a step back and I‚Äôm, like, wait ‚Äî I‚Äôm goated.‚Äù ‚ÄîMusician EKKSTACY (@ekkstacy)

My song ‚ÄòI walk this earth all by myself‚Äô changed my life very quickly. I went from working a 9-to-5 in Vancouver to being able to tour and live in LA,‚Äù says EKKSTACY, whose sound embraces ‚Äúelements of indie, punk and shoegaze and a few other things.‚Äù
 
‚ÄúI‚Äôm not trying to do anything or force anything, I‚Äôm the most impulsive person that I know. I just do what I want in the moment. It works well for me. I‚Äôve always been this way. There‚Äôs no plan for me.
 
I like bringing people together. I like seeing everyone having fun and seeing everyone happy. When I do a show and there are 1,000 kids having fun, I did that.‚Äù
